commit.message: Bump and release 0.19.5

Bump the slsa-github-generator action version

In the hope this solves a publishing error.

Bugfix development restarting when commands are passed

This ensures the script is placed before the commands (so the commands
are passed to the script).

Add a test to demonstrate sending files via the test client

This should ensure that it does work as expected.

Allow kwargs to be passed to the test client

This matches the Flask API (and the test_cli_runner API).

Correct the config_class type

It was incorrectly left as the Flask type when switching Quart to be
based on Flask.

Restore teardown_websocket methods

These were mistakenly removed when basing Quart on Flask.
Fix typo in documentation

Bugfix ensure request files are closed

By adding a close method to requests and call on cleanup. This mirrors
the method in Flask and ensures that any files opened for the request
e.g. when parsing body data files are closed.
Add final linting fix

Fix issues with the latest black, mypy, and pytest

This allows the tox tests to pass once again.

Remove obsolete `mock` dependency

Remove the dependency on `mock` package, as the test suite uses only
the builtin `unittest.mock` module.
Fix `DeprecationWarning` from `datetime.utcnow()` use
Bump and release 0.19.4

Add a shutdown event to the app

This is a pattern I've found myself using in my codebases to indicate
when the shutdown is called. This is useful as it allows background
tasks to wait on this event and shut themself down when set.
Fix issues with the latest mypy

Upgrade to 3.12 for CI/docs etc

Follows d01621d7e44d20266278c99b457b7e927dcd50c9
Bump to Python 3.12 for base tox actions

Improve the typing of the ensure_async method

This seems to hit a mypy error,
https://github.com/python/mypy/issues/16282, whereby a union input is
widened rather than narrowed by the override options - hence the type
ignores.

Fix the typing for AfterWebsocket functions

They can accept None as an argument if the websocket handler does not
return a response.

Remove is_coroutine_function

This was a workaround for Python versions pre 3.8.

Fix program not closing on Ctrl+C in Windows

The _windows_signal_support() loops forever. Using asyncio.gather make that trying to use Ctrl+C to end the program on Windows was just soft-blocking it after closing every other part of the program. The only choice was then to close the terminal window.

_windows_signal_support() was introduced on commit https://github.com/pallets/quart/commit/68da65c9da6f6efe2327c2db2154e88f6297085b to fix an issue on python 3.7. The function was removed since Quart doesn't support 3.7 since 0.19.0.

Closes: https://github.com/pallets/quart/issues/282

Co-authored-by: Julien Castiaux <Julien.castiaux@gmail.com>

Fix flake8 blocking commits

flake8 was blocking any commit during pre-commit check with error :

flake8...................................................................Failed
- hook id: flake8
- exit code: 1

src/quart/app.py:775:13: B028 No explicit stacklevel argument found. The warn method from the warnings module uses a stacklevel of 1 by default. This will only show a stack trace for the line on which the warn method is called. It is therefore recommended to use a stacklevel of 2 or greater to provide more information to the user.
Bump and release 0.19.3

Update the default config to better match Flask

EXPLAIN_TEMPLATE_LOADING was missing and APPLICATION_ROOT now safely
defaults to `/`.
Bump and release 0.19.2

Correctly set the cli Group in Quart

This was mistakenly set to Flask's in the Flask Sansio Scaffold, hence
Quart needs to override it to its own.
